1
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:17,440
Hello.

2
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:21,760
Stop!

3
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:31,960
Officer.

4
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,480
About You Kundee...

5
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:35,680
It really has nothing to do with me.

6
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,720
How did you know

7
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,040
we wanted to ask you about You Kundee?

8
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,360
That he was killed...

9
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:42,680
It's all over the internet.

10
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,120
It's hard not to know.

11
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:46,240
If You Kundee's case has nothing to do with you,

12
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,120
then why did you run?

13
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,000
Before the incident,

14
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:51,920
I had a bit of a conflict with him.

15
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:53,280
I...

16
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:55,040
I was afraid you would pin this

17
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:56,320
on me.

18
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,040
What exactly happened?

19
00:01:58,240 --> 00:01:59,600
I heard his club

20
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,800
had two fighters who were pretty good.

21
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,840
I just wanted them

22
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,320
to transfer to my club.

23
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,200
Let's go.

24
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:17,600
Boss.

25
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,080
About what I mentioned last time,

26
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,080
have you thought about it?

27
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:31,040
Money isn't a problem.

28
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:33,600
I won't shortchange you.

29
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:35,880
Boss,

30
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,520
who doesn't want to make money?

31
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,240
But...

32
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,680
But I can't agree to it.

33
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,080
The kids are all injured.

34
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,440
They really can't fight anymore.

35
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,880
That's a pretty poor excuse.

36
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,960
If you can't hand them over,

37
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,880
don't expect to stay in Tuo Cheng.

38
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,880
You met at Ancient Temple Street?

39
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:56,800
Yes.

40
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,440
After I let You Kundee

41
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,520
out of the car,

42
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,440
I saw him go into Zhiyin Bar.

43
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:03,680
As for the rest,

44
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:05,240
I really don't know.

45
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,080
Where did you go after the meeting?

46
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,240
After talking to him,

47
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,320
I rushed to the airport.

48
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:14,160
I flew to Mang Shan that same night.

49
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,960
You can check my plane tickets.

50
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,520
Those two fighters...

51
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,400
were they really injured?

52
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:24,120
Afterwards,

53
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,800
I sent someone to ask around.

54
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:28,200
There was no more news of them in Tuo Cheng.

55
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,000
The gym needs money to operate.

56
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,680
That boss offered so much money,

57
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,880
and the two fighters could

58
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:48,080
go to a better platform.

59
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,760
Why did You Kundee refuse?

60
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,000
You Kundee was telling the truth.

61
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,800
Those two fighters were really injured.

62
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,760
I see what you mean.

63
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,040
You're saying

64
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:02,080
our previous analysis was correct.

65
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,320
Those two fighters

66
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,480
were really abused to death by You Kundee.

67
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,800
But where's the evidence?

68
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,040
If Lin Wan's son

69
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,360
was really abused,

70
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,560
she would have taken him

71
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:13,680
to the hospital for treatment.

72
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,640
Maybe if we go to the hospital,

73
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:16,640
we can find evidence.

74
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,440
Found it.

75
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,480
This child...

76
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,520
one year ago,

77
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,680
was hospitalized for a fracture.

78
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,080
I see so many patients every day.

79
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,280
Fractures are a common occurrence.

80
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,400
The child you're talking about,

81
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,120
I don't remember.

82
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,520
I remember now.

83
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,560
I remember this boy.

84
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,480
He fell while skateboarding.

85
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,000
Didn't you say you usually

86
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,080
see too many patients?

87
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:57,920
Why do you have such a

88
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,080
strong impression of this child?

89
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,040
Generally speaking, patients

90
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,400
want to get better quickly.

91
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,200
But this little boy

92
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,560
refused to cooperate with treatment.

93
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,080
His mother cried a lot because of it.

94
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,400
So I remember it quite clearly.

95
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:08,640
So,

96
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:11,360
did he really fall while skateboarding?

97
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,280
I found it strange at the time too.

98
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,040
Why would skateboarding

99
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,240
cause such a serious injury?

100
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,680
Was it very serious?

101
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:18,840
I remember

102
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:20,400
the bone was broken.

103
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,280
We put a cast on it.

104
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,520
It took nearly half a year to heal.

105
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,440
Then is it possible

106
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:26,000
it was caused by something else?

107
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,440
Well...

108
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:28,800
it's hard to say.

109
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:30,040
After all, every patient's

110
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,200
injury situation is different,

111
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,320
and the severity varies too.

112
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,440
Is there a possibility

113
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,800
that he was abused?

114
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,680
His mother cherished him so much,

115
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:42,880
so abuse seems unlikely.

116
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:43,880
Besides, if we found

117
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,000
any signs of abuse,

118
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,120
we would report it immediately.

119
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:48,320
Then,

120
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,760
is there a possibility

121
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:50,760
that someone beforehand

122
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,120
covered up the traces of abuse?

123
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,360
Patient records are all networked.

124
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,400
We can see them all.

125
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:56,800
However,

126
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,800
this boy

127
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,320
doesn't seem to have been to the hospital much.

128
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:01,520
Thank you.

129
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,400
Sorry to trouble you, Doctor.

130
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,640
Public hospitals are networked,

131
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,120
but private clinics aren't.

132
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:28,080
The private clinics found online

133
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,400
are just these few.

134
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,240
These are just the ones on the surface.

135
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,760
There are many illegal clinics

136
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,080
whose names you can't find online.

137
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:39,400
Searching them one by one like this

138
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,000
would be a huge waste of time.

139
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,600
As for Ma Nuo and Mei Dong,

140
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,640
is there any news?

141
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,880
They are still monitoring Lin Wan.

142
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,200
No news so far.

143
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,760
How come Lin Wan

144
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,440
hasn't made a move at all?

145
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,320
Didn't you just advise me?

146
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,640
Surveillance

147
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:23,120
requires patience.

148
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,400
A moving company?

149
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,440
Is she trying to run away?

150
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:01,480
Sir.

151
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:02,800
Upstairs.

152
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:03,880
Okay.

153
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,080
Here, let me help.

154
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,400
Something's up with Lin Wan.

155
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:24,240
What's the situation?

156
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:31,240
A moving truck came this afternoon.

157
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:33,640
Lin Wan took the kids and moved out first.

158
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:34,800
Ma Nuo is following them right now.

159
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,200
Then I went to the real estate agency.

160
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,760
She sold this house.

161
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:40,640
Sold it?

162
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:41,880
Sold it.

163
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:44,120
But I think it makes sense.

164
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:46,000
After all, her husband died.

165
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,400
She wants a change of environment.

166
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,440
A change of mood.

167
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,960
When did she...

168
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,640
...list the house with the agency?

169
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,520
The day after You Kundee died.

170
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,320
Is there a problem with that?

171
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,320
The day after.

172
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,160
Even we didn't know...

173
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,680
...who the deceased was yet.

174
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,680
Lin Wan being in such a rush to sell the house...

175
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,120
...only proves one thing.

176
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:11,200
She knew You Kundee wasn't coming back.

177
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:17,400
You Kundee's home is accessible by van.

178
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:18,920
Presumably, a heavy truck...

179
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:20,000
...could enter as well.

180
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:25,000
And his house is only...

181
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,200
...500 meters from Ancient Temple Street.

182
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,000
Are you suspecting...

183
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,520
...that You Kundee's home...

184
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,120
...is the primary crime scene?

185
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:35,680
Impossible.

186
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:38,240
I've checked everything upstairs.

187
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:40,000
There were no clues at all.

188
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:42,520
If Lin Wan really is the killer,

189
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,880
she would have wiped those traces long ago.

190
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,840
Why would she wait for us to check?

191
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,120
What about the courtyard?

192
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,200
Court...

193
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,240
The c-c-courtyard hasn't been...

194
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,880
It stinks.

195
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:14,760
Are you okay?

196
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:18,880
The water smells.

197
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,200
There's something wrong with this water.

198
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,400
It's You Kundee's limbs.

199
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,280
Looks like this is the primary crime scene.

200
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,240
Bones sink in a pool of blood,

201
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,720
soul nailed to an iron mountain.

202
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:48,880
Resentment never ceases,

203
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:50,120
torment never ends.

204
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,160
Pain is ever new,

205
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,520
despair is eternal.

206
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:55,160
What does this mean?

207
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:58,280
The talisman tattooed on You Kundee's limbs...

208
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,160
...combined with the severed limbs...

209
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,240
...and the crushed torso...

210
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,760
...is the occult arts to open the gates of Naraka.

211
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,280
Naraka is...

212
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,880
...a place of suffering similar to hell.

213
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,560
Sinners will follow...

214
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,400
...karma to endure various torments.

215
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,000
Heart gouging, dismemberment...

216
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,120
...being crushed by iron.

217
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,640
Legend has it that those under the spell...

218
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:16,520
...will be trapped inside and tortured for eternity.

219
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,600
Then why was his torso...

220
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:21,400
...dumped on Ancient Temple Street?

221
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:24,120
Perhaps that signifies the beginning of his evil deeds.

222
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,760
He seems to be clutching something in his hand.

223
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,640
It must be from when he struggled...

224
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:47,920
...and ripped off the killer's button.

225
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,640
Let's look for anything else.

226
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:00,920
This is...

227
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,160
...an abused stuffed toy.

228
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,760
A damaged doll.

229
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,640
Placed together with You Kundee's limbs.

230
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,240
It must have some kind of connection...

231
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,600
...to this case.

232
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,600
You mean...

233
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:21,120
...Lin Wan did all this?

234
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:24,120
But doing all this...

235
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,920
...what special meaning does it have?

236
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:52,480
Kano.

237
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,480
Kano.

238
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,400
How many times have I told you?

239
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:05,520
Told you not to do this.

240
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:08,000
Why just won't you listen?

241
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:40,720
Pa Xin.

242
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,120
I found something here.

243
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,040
Okay.

244
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,240
These dolls...

245
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:52,760
...what do they have to do with the case?

246
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,400
Sis.

247
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:29,400
Why did you commit suicide?

248
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:34,040
Who exactly harmed you?
